@flexiarg coordination/bounded-execution
@title Bounded Execution (G2)
@keywords budget, execution, bounded, timeout, sandbox
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/error-hierarchy futon-theory/stop-the-line]

! conclusion:
  If you want safe and predictable coordination, execute tasks under explicit budgets (time, tokens, side effects) and reject when budgets are exceeded.

  + context: Coordination must treat execution as a resource-consuming action with a defined budget.
  + IF:
    you want an execution gate that cannot run away or wedge the system

  + HOWEVER:
    unbounded execution produces unpredictable latency and failure modes that break multi-agent systems

  + THEN:
    enforce a budget at G2 and short-circuit with a typed rejection when exceeded

  + BECAUSE:
    budgets create selection pressure and prevent hidden coordination costs

